			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was thinking about this. Isn't pet discipline more of a pet-caster archetype than a class AA? Class AA's for everyone except mages  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" />  are very class-oriented. Wake the Dead, DC etc. Only the only class AA given to several disparate classes is /pet hold. Even quick damage, which was wiz/dru only until recently, is an archetype. 
<br />

<br />
The benefit of moving pet hold to archetype is that it becomes a 12pt (6+6) "you can raid now"  AA as opposed to the current 24pts (6+12+6). 
<br />

<br />
This struck home over the weekend when I died 4 times on a Bert (codb) raid because non-/pet hold pets were banned and I drew sit-agro on a couple unannounced pulls (codb is indoors, so no horse). If I'd had a pet, it could've pulled the mob off me, giving the offtanks time to establish agro.
<br />

<br />
Thoughts?
<br />

<br />
