				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I think they should have /pet hold as innate, and not an AA at all.
<br />

<br />
/rant on
<br />

<br />
The other alternative which I would find acceptable would be to give every non-pet class an AA called "You can raid now", which would mean that if you do NOT have it, and you are in a raid of more than 2 groups, then for melees it would be like having no armour on, with gimped defense and dodge skills, and their DPS output is gimped by about 40%.  And for all other casters, the mana cost off all their spells jumps about 40%, and the healers maybe have about 40% less effective heals.  This would be a class-level AA costing 6 points, just like pet discipline.
<br />

<br />
Or you could eliminate pet discipline, since it is REQUIRED on raids, and mages without their pets are 60% (or LESS) of what they are with them.  If you force us to be gimped by REQUIRING a certain AA before we can raid (FEW raid leaders will allow pets if the owner doesn't have pet discipline, and sometimes not even then), then require everybody else to do the same.
<br />

<br />
Pet discipline isn't something that's "nice to have", but is an absolute class essential ability.  There is no other AA for anybody else that is like that.  AAs are supposed to ENHANCE your character, not just make them "no longer gimped".
<br />

<br />
/rant off
<br />

<br />
Yes it is militant, but it is also true.<br />_________________<br />Eriol Telcontar
